oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Senator John F. Kennedy at the Maxwell House Hotel
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Senator Kennedy visited Nashville in the late winter of 1959. He spoke at a sold out Democratic party banquet at the Maxwell House Hotel in downtown Nashville. Mayor Ben West acted as toastmaster for the event. 3 x 4 in.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Kennedy, John F.; West, Ben
Nashville (Tenn.)
